  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of this study is to evaluate the utility of the Banyan UCH-L1/GFAP
      Detection Assay as an aid in the evaluation of suspected traumatic brain injury (Glasgow Coma
      Scale score 9-15) in conjunction with other clinical information within 12 hours of injury to
      assist in determining the need for a CT scan of the head.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
